p: The labeled peptide fragments were mixed, and 15 components were separated using the Agilent 1200 HPLC separation system. The chromatographic column was a high-pH RP C18 (4.6 mm × 250 mm, 5 μm, 300 A). Mobile phase A was the aqueous phase containing 20 mM ammonium acetate (pH 10). Mobile phase B was ACN/water containing 20 mM ammonium acetate (ACN/Water, 9/1, v/ v, pH 10). The mobile phase gradient was 5% B to 35% B and 35%–40% B to 90% B; 90% B was then maintained for 10 minutes. The fractionated samples were desalinated using Ziptip solid-phase microextraction and analyzed.
